        "content": "<p>I ran into a universe issue when trying to apply <code>gaussianReal_neg</code>:</p>\n<p>In <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Probability/Distributions/Gaussian/Real.html#ProbabilityTheory.gaussianReal_neg\">Probability.Distributions.Gaussian.Real</a>, line 350 states:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">Ω</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">mΩ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MeasurableSpace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ω</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Measure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ω</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ω</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Should <code>Type</code> be changed <code>Type*</code> here? More generally, how can I determine whether an instance of <code>Type</code> should actually be <code>Type*</code>?</p>",
        "id": 572871463,
        "sender_full_name": "Joris van Winden",
        "timestamp": 1770666161
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes it should be <code>Type*</code>. This is a clear typo. Everything should use <code>Type*</code>, unless there is a good reason for <code>Type</code> (and I never encounter any in probability files).</p>",
        "id": 572871876,
        "sender_full_name": "Rémy Degenne",
        "timestamp": 1770666300
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Please make a PR!</p>",
        "id": 572871921,
        "sender_full_name": "Rémy Degenne",
        "timestamp": 1770666317
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think assumptions should never use <code>Type</code> in Mathlib.<br>\nIn proofs, and as return types, there can be good uses for <code>Type</code>.</p>",
        "id": 572871995,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1770666334
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is this something which could be caught by a linter (possibly restricted to certain folders)?</p>\n<p>To illustrate: when searching for <code>: Type}</code> in VSCode, I get 341 results in 140 files. Most are in <code>CategoryTheory</code>, but there are also some in e.g. <code>Analysis/Specialfunctions/ExpDeriv</code>, <code>Analysis/Fourier/AddCircle</code>, <code>MeasureTheory/Measure/WithDensity</code> where I suspect it should be <code>Type*</code> instead.</p>",
        "id": 572874336,
        "sender_full_name": "Joris van Winden",
        "timestamp": 1770667113
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess as long as there are not too many it can be handled on a case by case basis.</p>",
