    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"112680\">Johan Commelin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Type.20typo/near/572871995\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think assumptions should never use <code>Type</code> in Mathlib.<br>\nIn proofs, and as return types, there can be good uses for <code>Type</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In parts of representation theory you have to have k and G or G and M in the same universe, and then if one of them is the integers or complexes...</p>",
